spec: abc_extra176
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(abc)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html — Python abc module documentation"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source: Lib/abc.py"
  notes:
    - "This spec covers: abc.ABCMeta class identity and abc.get_cache_token function identity — ABCMeta.__name__=='ABCMeta' (len=7); ABCMeta.__module__=='abc'; ABCMeta.__qualname__=='ABCMeta'; ABCMeta.__bases__[0].__name__=='type' (ABCMeta is a metaclass inheriting from type); get_cache_token.__name__=='get_cache_token' (len=15); get_cache_token.__module__=='_abc' (implemented in C extension _abc); get_cache_token.__qualname__=='get_cache_token'; get_cache_token.__class__.__name__=='builtin_function_or_method'."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__name__ == 'ABCMeta' (len=7: A-B-C-M-e-t-a). ABCMeta is the metaclass for defining Abstract Base Classes; it inherits from the built-in 'type' metaclass. Its __module__ is 'abc'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "abc.get_cache_token.__name__ == 'get_cache_token' (len=15: g-e-t-_-c-a-c-h-e-_-t-o-k-e-n). get_cache_token returns the current ABC cache token (an integer that increments when ABCs are registered). Its __module__ is '_abc' (the C extension backing module), not 'abc'. Its __class__.__name__ is 'builtin_function_or_method'. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "abc.ABCMeta.__bases__[0].__name__ == 'type'. ABCMeta is a metaclass — it is itself an instance of type and inherits from type. This is what allows ABCMeta to be used as a metaclass when constructing ABC subclasses. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "abc.get_cache_token.__module__ == '_abc' (not 'abc'). The get_cache_token function is implemented in the C extension module _abc for performance; the pure-Python abc module re-exports it. Verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
    - "All expected values verified with Python 3.14.3 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-11."
  created_at: "2026-04-11T00:00:00Z"

error_model: python_exceptions

